sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist/CI System
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant Master as Training Master Pod<br/>Framework-specific
    participant Worker as Training Worker Pods<br/>Framework-specific
    participant Storage as External Storage<br/>S3/NFS 443/TCP or NFS

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 1: User Submits PyTorchJob

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>kubectl apply<br/>User Credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate/*<br/>mTLS<br/>API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate/*<br/>mTLS<br/>API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutation Response
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job Created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: WATCH PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: PyTorchJob Event

    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Service<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Service Created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Master Pod<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Master Pod Created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Worker Pods Created

    Note over Master,Worker: Flow 4: Training Job Execution

    Master->>Storage: Load Dataset<br/>443/TCP HTTPS or NFS<br/>AWS IAM or NFS auth
    Storage-->>Master: Dataset

    Worker->>Storage: Load Dataset<br/>443/TCP HTTPS or NFS<br/>AWS IAM or NFS auth
    Storage-->>Worker: Dataset

    Worker->>Master: Distributed Training Communication<br/>23456/TCP (PyTorch)<br/>Framework-dependent auth
    Master-->>Worker: Gradient Updates

    Master->>Storage: Save Checkpoint<br/>443/TCP HTTPS or NFS<br/>AWS IAM or NFS auth
    Storage-->>Master: Checkpoint Saved

    Controller->>K8sAPI: UPDATE PyTorchJob Status<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Status Updated

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP<br/>No Auth
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus Metrics<br/>(job counts, reconciliation times)

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 3: Gang Scheduling (Optional)

    participant Volcano as Volcano Scheduler<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS

    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE PodGroup CR<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: PodGroup Created

    Volcano->>K8sAPI: WATCH PodGroup<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Volcano: PodGroup Event

    Volcano->>K8sAPI: Schedule All Pods Together<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Volcano: Pods Scheduled
